===Noun===
'''nave''' (plural [[naves]])
#The middle or body of a church, extending from the [[transept]]s to the principal entrances.

====Etymology====
Ultimately from Latin ''[[navis]]'', via a Romance source.

====Translations====
*French: [[nef]]
*German: [[Schiff]]

===Noun===
'''nave''' (plural [[naves]])

#A [[hub]] of a [[wheel]] <!--as in "bowl the round nave" from Hamlet--->

====Etymology====
Old English ''[[nafu]]''. Cognates include Dutch [[naaf]] and German [[Nabe]].

